### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
what are the verb tenses?

### Response:


There are several types of verbs in English, but some common ones include present tense (e.g., walk, run), past tense (e.g., walked, ran), future tense (e.g., will walk, will have walked), and present perfect tense (e.g., have/has/have had). Additionally, there are auxiliary verbs that help to form different tenses (e.g., do, did, can, could, shall, should, will, would, etc.).
